.TH "xdr_shrink_bufhead" 9 "xdr_shrink_bufhead" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xdr_shrink_bufhead \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" xdr_shrink_bufhead
.BI "(struct xdr_buf *buf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
xdr_buf
.IP "len" 12
new length of buf->head[0]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Shrinks XDR buffer's header kvec buf->head[0], setting it to
'len' bytes. The extra data is not lost, but is instead
moved into the inlined pages and/or the tail.
